history.content:
I have asked Prof Hartmann to create a Piazza post for you all which he will likely do next week.

Until then, I have posted @10558

Please keep in mind that enrollment priority is given to EECS/CS declared majors through the end of phase 2. In the event that a seat becomes available before Jan 6th, the first waitlisted EECS/CS major will automatically be moved into the seat before anyone who does not meet the reserve capacity requirement. So, in theory, even though you show as position 70 on the WL right now. If no one ahead of you on the wait list is an EECS/CS major, as a CS major you would be moved into the next available seat. (I know - this is a highly unlikely scenario. I use it for explanation purposes only.)

Once the adjustment period begins on January 6th, the reserve capacities come down. Only then will the wait list be processed in sequential order based on position.

I know there have been a lot of posts regarding CS160 enrollment, but I wanted to know when we can get an answer to these enrollment questions. I am also a senior CS major who is currently waitlisted (70+ number), and it's very unlikely that I will get into the class since the class was expanded to take 35 people from the waitlist last semester. It even seems like some of my peers who are non-cs majors but with earlier enrollment times are waitlisted before me and other graduating cs majors. I understand that this is a difficult issue for the CS department, but is there a timeline for when can we hear back about the class expansion (if there is one) or the waitlist situation so we could plan our schedules accordingly? Thank you for your time!
history.subject: CS160 Enrollment
